# All Page URL - WordPress Plugin

All Page URL is a powerful WordPress plugin designed to display all page URLs, post URLs, and category URLs in an organized and easy-to-read table format within your WordPress admin panel. This plugin enhances the user experience by providing a seamless way to view and export URLs for better content management and sharing.

## Features
- Displays all page URLs with publication date, page ID, title, and URL.
- Displays all post URLs with publication date, post ID, title, and URL.
- Displays all category URLs with category ID, title, and URL.
- Organized table format for easy navigation and readability.
- Export options to download URLs as CSV or Excel files.
- Simple and intuitive admin interface.
- Lightweight and efficient, ensuring minimal impact on site performance.

## Installation
1. Download the plugin from GitHub.
2. Upload the `all-page-url` folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory.
3. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.
4. Navigate to the "Show All URLs" menu item in the WordPress admin panel to view and manage your URLs.

## Usage
- View all URLs for pages, posts, and categories in separate tables.
- Use the export buttons to download URLs in CSV or Excel format for easy sharing and analysis.

## Contribute
Feel free to contribute to the development of this plugin by submitting issues or pull requests on the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/your-github-username/all-page-url).

